      "raw_text": "chin\" allied with the movement.\n\n\nOn the day of election, while the\npaid workers for the saloon were\nrounding up the vote. the temperance\nside depended upon prayer meetings\nat most of the churches. While the\nwomen of the city, who stood almost\nas a unit in an organized band to\nassist the ordinance, prayed, the men\nvoted. The result, S466 dry\" votes\nagainst 5,270 wet\" offers food for\nreflection on the subject of the eff\ncacy of prayer as a potent force in\npolitics"
